HEADWORD: Cuesta
<hw>Cues"ta</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp.]</ety> <def>A
sloping plain, esp. one with the upper end at the crest of a cliff; a
hill or ridge with one face steep and the opposite face gently
sloping.</def> <mark>[Southwestern U. S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
